<sections><clause id="_376ca7d2-c1d3-42a7-acf5-828d8627355b" unnumbered="true" obligation="normative" displayorder="1">

<p id="_0f5fceb7-6f71-46e3-b2ec-a4a6341e3805"><strong>Absorbing molecule <sup>127</sup>I<sub>2</sub>, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mtext>a</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></stem> component, P(62) 17-1 transition</strong><fn reference="1"><p id="_8d1fa24b-b69d-4617-a42b-31a105fee72f">All transitions in I<sub>2</sub> refer to the <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#928;</mo><mtext>&#160;</mtext><msubsup><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msubsup><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mtext>&#160;</mtext><msubsup><mrow><mo>&#931;</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msubsup></math></stem> system.</p></fn></p>
</clause>
<clause id="_cipm_recommended_values" obligation="normative" displayorder="2"><title depth="1">1.<tab/>CIPM recommended values</title><dl id="_c42c5694-9d36-49b8-9e86-da679cfcb5d8">
<dt>The values</dt>
<dd>
<p id="_8fd3e2d6-16aa-4280-bed0-43806ef9b6ba"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>520&#8239;206&#8239;808.4</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_MHz"><mi mathvariant="normal">MHz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem><br/>
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mo>=</mo><mn>576&#8239;294&#8239;760.4</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_fm"><mi mathvariant="normal">fm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem></p>
</dd>
</dl>
<p id="_369b1df0-ba1b-4a79-9930-0a7528859f1b">with a relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>&#8722;</mi><mn>10</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem> apply to the radiation of a dye laser (or frequency-doubled He-Ne laser) stabilized with an iodine cell, within or external to the laser, having a cold-finger temperature of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu23"><mi mathvariant="normal">&#176;C</mi></mrow>









</math></stem><fn reference="2"><p id="_6e1945e0-ffa6-4075-8eb6-dc016d3328f8">For the specification of operating conditions, such as temperature, modulation width and laser power, the symbols &#177; refer to a tolerance, not an uncertainty.</p></fn>.</p></clause>
